cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about text generation using a generative adversarial network (GAN) with a focus on promoting diversity and avoiding repetition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes a novel discriminator based on language models, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of GANs suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and the application of the method to review and dialogue generation could also relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
